<%#
  Persistent logout affordance for every authenticated shell (staff header +
  both portal layouts) — SessionsController#destroy requires authentication
  already (not in allow_unauthenticated_access), so this is the only gate
  that matters; no authorize!/entitlement check applies to ending your own
  session. A plain <a> with turbo_method (same idiom as
  identity_access/roster_imports#show), NOT button_to — this renders in the
  layout header on every page, and a <form> there would collide with pages
  that assert "no form on this read-only surface" (e.g. finance/assignments
  portal specs).
-%>
<%= link_to "Cerrar sesión", session_path, data: { turbo_method: :delete }, class: "self-service-link" %>
